# plugin.json Template

This file goes in `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` at the root of every plugin.

## Fields

- **name**: Kebab-case identifier for the plugin (e.g., `coding-with-node`)
- **version**: Semver version string
  - **patch** (0.0.X): Bug fixes, typo corrections, minor wording changes
  - **minor** (0.X.0): New skills, commands, agents, or features
  - **major** (X.0.0): Breaking changes (renamed skills, restructured directories, removed features)
- **description**: One-line summary of what the plugin provides
- **author.name**: Author's display name
- **author.email**: Author's contact email
- **homepage**: URL to the plugin's documentation or landing page
- **repository**: URL to the source code repository
- **license**: SPDX license identifier (typically `MIT`)
- **keywords**: Array of discovery terms for marketplace search

## Template

```json
{
  "name": "{{plugin-name}}",
  "version": "{{semver}}",
  "description": "{{one-line description}}",
  "author": {
    "name": "{{author name}}",
    "email": "{{email}}"
  },
  "homepage": "{{url}}",
  "repository": "{{github url}}",
  "license": "MIT",
  "keywords": ["{{keyword1}}", "{{keyword2}}"]
}
```
